content.description: Powerful sit start to an engaging top out. Short but enjoyable problem.
content.location: On the right side of the boulder, find the low crack jug for your right hand and a good left hand edge. Sit start using some trickery and head straight up.

content.description: Short little line but it has some nice movement and cool holds.
content.location: On the left side of the boulder, look for an obvious and large triangle block. Stand start matched on this and work the short arete to the top.

content.description: A little contrived. After opening move to lip, stay low and bounce out to large sidepull rail near the triangle block of Lame Stand. Once your left hand is on the sidepull rail, then use the holds on or above the lip. From there top out.
content.location: Same start as Lamer. Trend left into Lame Stand.

content.description: Low/sit start. Fun one mover into the stand.
content.location: Find a good left hand side pull under the small roof and a right hand slot edge. Pick which small and high feet you want to use and crank into the starting triangle pinch of the stand. Low supporting blocks are off for feet.

content.description: This boulder is right off the Summit Rock Trail. There are 4 problems on this boulder. The boulder is often shaded and protected from the weather. Because it is right off the trail, you will see many people hiking by you on their way to the top of Summit Rock.
